# Rules vs Runtime Context Layering

- `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`: long-lived, reusable, cross-task facts and constraints only.
- `.cursor/skills/*/SKILL.md`: structured execution flows for stable, repeatable processes.
- `docs/playbooks/*/playbook.md`: evolving tactical experience organized by domain — survives task archival, helps agents reproduce successful patterns. Scripts in the same folder automate repeated checks.
- `docs/dependencies/*.md`: external library versions, APIs, deprecation notes — refreshed via Context7.
- `docs/workspace/**`: human decision and draft workspace — progress narrative, pending decisions with trade-offs, decision log, intent hypotheses, brainstorm summaries, concise dialogue traces, rich media assets. Organized by workflow in subfolders. Write access restricted to parent orchestrator; subagents supply material via `decision_candidates` in handoff. See `docs/workspace/README.md`.
- `docs/requirements/*.md`: user-facing interaction layer — concise user intent, progress, status, blockers, next steps.
- `docs/tasks/*.md`: primary carrier for task-scoped runtime context — plans, execution scope, validation state, review conclusions.
- Allowed in rules: verified local dev-environment facts, frozen repo-level business rules, long-lived orchestration constraints.
- Allowed in playbooks: non-obvious execution patterns, anti-patterns, validation tips, edge cases — things that are useful across tasks but may still evolve.
- Allowed in workspace: decision context, trade-off analysis, option comparison, decision rationale, draft thinking, intent hypotheses, concise dialogue traces, progress narrative for human readers, supporting data tables and images.
- Workspace `draft.md` is the discovery layer; do not treat it as confirmed requirement truth or task-runtime handoff.
- Never put runtime context in rules or playbooks: current task plans, temp blockers, one-off test failures, local workarounds, branch state.
- Shared runtime info for multiple subagents goes in `docs/tasks/*.md` or parent handoff, not rules.
- Concise user-facing stage status syncs to `docs/requirements/*.md`, not left only in chat history.
- Decision-relevant findings (trade-offs, options, human-intervention needs) sync to `docs/workspace/**`, not left only in task docs or chat history.
- Promote playbook entry to rule only when confirmed to hold across future tasks and contains no secrets.
